From ffe2314ff280eacdfaa5143ee4229d4e9ba9617a Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Cursor Agent <cursoragent@cursor.com>
Date: Sat, 4 Apr 2026 03:06:34 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 1/5] fix(security): harden Stripe webhook signature, auth
 validation, CORS, and notifications
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

- Fix Stripe webhook timingSafeEqual buffer length mismatch (compare hex strings)
- Fix SMS endpoint sending email addresses instead of phone numbers
- Add requireJson, rejectOversizedBody, isValidEmail to auth/index.js
- Restrict CORS preview origin echo to *.vercel.app only
- Fix notifications processPending using nested objects instead of flat columns
- Use centralized N8N_BASE from _config.js in stripe-webhook.js and intake.js
- Remove unused sanitize import from intake.js
- Add error logging in auth/session.js
- Fix about.html JSON-LD schema Person → Organization
- Fix partners.html form success shown on HTTP error
- Add keyboard a11y (role=button, tabindex, Enter/Space) to all FAQ accordions
- Consolidate duplicate test/ into tests/, port tryDeterministicAnswer tests
- Fix misleading comments in compliance.test.js
- Remove || true from CI lint step so failures break the build
